benefits.title: Pest and Pathogen Independence (Measured by Phylogenetic Diversity)
benefits.message: 40th percentile (Faith's PD: 804.28) - Plants have some close relatives (fair phylogenetic diversity)
benefits.detail: Several plants share recent evolutionary history. Related plants often share susceptibility to the same pests and pathogens, though the guild is not critically clustered.

benefits.title: Growth Strategy Compatibility
benefits.detail: CSR strategies measure how plants allocate resources to Competitive growth, Stress tolerance, or Ruderal (disturbance) strategies. Guild composition: 3 Competitive-dominant (high CSR values: >75th percentile). Some potential conflicts detected - see CSR Strategy Profile below for details and recommendations.

benefits.title: Natural Insect Pest Control
benefits.detail: Plants attract beneficial insects (predators and parasitoids) that naturally suppress pest populations. Excellent biocontrol - abundant predators and parasitoids provide strong pest suppression

benefits.title: Natural Disease Suppression
benefits.message: 98th percentile pathogen control via 47 antagonistic mechanisms
benefits.detail: Plants harbor beneficial fungi that antagonize pathogens, reducing disease incidence through biological control. Excellent disease suppression - abundant antagonistic fungi provide strong pathogen control

benefits.title: Beneficial Mycorrhizal Network
benefits.message: 512 shared beneficial fungal species connect 7 plants (100th percentile)
benefits.detail: Shared beneficial fungi (mycorrhizal partners, endophytes, and saprotrophs) create underground networks that facilitate nutrient exchange, water sharing, and chemical communication between plants. Excellent fungal network - abundant shared fungi create strong underground connections

benefits.title: Structural Diversity
benefits.message: 5 growth forms spanning 27.0m height range (100th percentile)
benefits.detail:
**Vertical Stratification (Quality: 1.00 - Excellent):**

**Canopy Layer (>15m):**
  - Quercus robur (Acorn Tree): 27.1m, EIVE-L: 6.2 (flexible)

**Understory (5-15m):**
  - Vitis vinifera (Common Grape): 9.7m, EIVE-L: 6.2 (flexible)

**Shrub Layer (1-5m):**
  - Coffea arabica (Arabian Coffee): 4.6m, EIVE-L: 6.9 (flexible)
  - Prunus spinosa (Blackthorn): 2.1m, EIVE-L: 7.1 (flexible)
  - Rosa canina (Canker Rose): 2.0m, EIVE-L: 7.2 (flexible)

**Ground Layer (<1m):**
  - Dactylis glomerata (Akaroa): 0.7m, EIVE-L: 6.8 (flexible)
  - Fragaria vesca (Alpine Strawberry): 0.1m, EIVE-L: 5.9 (flexible)

**Why this stratification works well:**
7 plants are flexible (EIVE-L 3.2-7.47) and tolerate partial shade. No sun-loving plants that would be shaded out.

Excellent structural diversity - multiple layers maximize space and light use

benefits.title: Pollinator Support
benefits.detail: Plants attract and support overlapping pollinator communities, ensuring reliable pollination services and promoting pollinator diversity. Excellent pollinator support - abundant shared pollinators ensure reliable pollination
